class="comment-text"><p>Well, this is a RIDICULOUS comparison.  Here&#8217;s why:  The Mac OS can function at faster speeds with better results with less than half of the internals of a Windows based PC.  I own a 5 year old MacBook, and have a first gen duo core processor, one gig of RAM, etc.  My Mac has REPEATEDLY outclassed the PC I own with a core duo, 3 gig of RAM, etc.  when it was stil running Windows, which it is NOT any longer. Reason?  Efficiency.  When you start your Windows machine, notice how your OS is Copyrighted in 1985?  Kinda like rebuilding a new house on top of an old foundation with old pipes, etc.  Windows 7 is still based on the foundation of the ORIGINAL Windows OS.  Architecture, plain and simple.  A FAIR comparison would be to compare a Windows PC versus that same PC running Linux (I.E.-Ubuntu), and compare speeds, costs of ownership, down time, etc.  If you&#8217;re gonna compare, compare Apples to Apples, or Windows to Linux&#8230;.not Apples to raisins (metaphor?  yep&#8230;)  Oh, and for the record, you can buy a MacBook Pro for considerably less that you have compared here above that will outspeed, and overall outclass the PC described, AND it&#8217;ll be mobile&#8230;so THERE!</p></div><div
class="reply"> <a
class='comment-reply-link' href='/blog/pc-vs-mac/?replytocom=23854#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-23854", "23854", "respond", "42254")'>Reply</a></div></div><div
class="after-comment"><div></div></div></div></li></li><li
id="comment-23862" ><div
